file=Governance/board/custom/constitution-enforcement/assets/constitution-template.md · [nc:[Business Name] Constitution — TEMPLATE=> **This is a template, not a constitution.** Nothing in it is in force until the operator\n> fills it in and saves it at the path configured in board's config (`constitution_path`).\n> Keep it short: a constitution is the handful of rules that should survive every quarterly\n> strategy change. If a rule needs frequent exceptions, it belongs in fiduciary-guard's\n> config thresholds instead — not here.\n\n**Version:** [v0.1]\n**Adopted:** [YYYY-MM-DD]\n**Owner:** [operator / founder name]\n\n · ar:Amendment Rule=[How this document changes. Example: "Amendments require the operator's explicit written\napproval, a one-line rationale, and a version bump. Board proposes; only the operator adopts."\nWithout a filled-in amendment rule, the constitution cannot be changed at all — write one.]\n\n · a:Articles=[3–10 articles is the healthy range. Each article needs all three parts — a bare statement\nwithout an operational test invites interpretation drift.]\n · ### Article 1 — [Short name]=- **Rule:** [One sentence, plain language. Example shape: "The business never …" /\n"No decision may … without …"]\n- **Test:** [How board checks a decision against it. "A decision violates this article if …"]\n- **Exceptions:** [Explicit and narrow, or "None." Undocumented exceptions don't exist.]\n · ### Article 2 — [Short name]=- **Rule:**\n- **Test:**\n- **Exceptions:**\n · ### Article 3 — [Short name]=- **Rule:**\n- **Test:**\n- **Exceptions:**\n\n[Add articles as needed — but every article added is a permanent enforcement burden;\nprefer fewer, harder rules.]\n\n · p:Precedence=[What wins when documents conflict. Suggested default: Constitution > locked strategy\ncommitments (strategic-veto) > config thresholds (fiduciary-guard) > everything else.]\n · cl:Clarifications Log=[When an UNCLEAR ruling gets resolved by the operator, record the resolution here so the\nsame ambiguity is never escalated twice.]\n · tb=\| Date \| Article \| Ambiguity \| Resolution \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|